{
  "message": "feat(web): scaffold Vite + React 19 UI shell\n\nAdds the initial `apps/web` frontend app shell.\n\nWhat\u2019s included\n- Vite + React baseline wiring:\n  - `apps/web/vite.config.ts` (react plugin + dev server port).\n  - `apps/web/index.html` entry with `#root` mount.\n  - `apps/web/src/main.tsx` bootstraps React (`createRoot`) and renders `App`.\n- Minimal placeholder UI:\n  - `apps/web/src/App.tsx` renders a \u201cscaffold is live\u201d placeholder.\n  - `apps/web/src/index.css` stub for future styling system adoption.\n- App-local workspace config:\n  - `apps/web/package.json` with `dev/build/preview/test` scripts.\n  - `apps/web/tsconfig.json` placeholder for app-specific overrides.\n- `apps/web/tests/README.md` stub describing where unit/component tests will live.\n\nIntent\n- Establish the frontend build/runtime boundary early (Vite + React 19) without committing to routing/state libraries yet.\n- Provide a stable target for future E2E smoke tests (UI boots + renders a deterministic placeholder).",
